# Rule Sync

Rules exist in three parallel directories that must stay identical:

- `.cursor/rules/` — Cursor
- `.agents/rules/` — Codex / generic agents
- `.claude/rules/` — Claude Code

When creating, editing, or deleting any rule file, apply the **same change** to all three directories. Also update `AGENTS.md` at the project root if the change affects a core rule documented there.

## Workflow

1. Make the change in `.cursor/rules/<file>.mdc`
2. Copy the identical file to `.agents/rules/<file>.mdc` and `.claude/rules/<file>.mdc`
3. If a rule is deleted, delete it from all three directories
4. If `AGENTS.md` documents the same rule, update it to match
